results.title: An Ocean Dream Catcher Poem
results.description:
An Ocean Dream Catcher Poem
Written by a Native Texan

Hanging by the window
My dream catcher waits
To catch me a dream that's hopefully great

Quiet and still it waits in the night
To catch a dream travelling in flight 

Its web is of leather, its feathers lite
The magic it works, carries great height

Will it bring me a lover, a funny story or song
Or, will it bring nightmares where everything goes wrong

The time is now near for me to lie down
And wait for a dream that's happy and sound

Dream catcher, dream catcher caution you please,
My heart is now calm, my mind is at ease

Go in the night and find what you will
Catch me a dream that's meaningful and still.


Esther Monsalve

results.title: Live Laugh Love wall decor vinyl decal home decor art stencil paint alternative DIY do it yourself project
results.description:
Only the best, easiest, and non permanent way to decorate your walls.  It is made of the highest quality indoor wall vinyl on the market.  The vinyl has a matte finish so it looks painted on when finished but will remove easily without leaving a mark.  Great for renters!!!!!

You will receive 6 separate decals:
1. Love Beyond words
2. Laugh every day
3. Live every moment
4. Bottom Line design
5. Butterfly
6. Hearts
*** test decal to check compatibility of paint

You can place them however you would like. Our total sizes offered are based on placement shown in picture.

*If you want a different size or color than the ones offered in the ad contact us.

*Installation is easy and the vinyl will not damage your paint or leave residue. You will receive detailed instructions and an install video link.

*We use high grade die cut calendered ORACAL 631 vinyl and guarantee your satisfaction 100%

*If you want a different size or color contact us.

*********************************************************************************************************
* Apply decals in area that is out of reach of small children.
* This product is one time application. The decals are removable, but not reusable. 
* Due to condition and age of walls prior to application, small damage may occur upon removal
* Our decals are made with high quality removable vinyl and are custom cut when purchased.
* Our removable high quality matte vinyl decals when applied to the wall look painted on!
* Removable wall decals can be applied to almost all clean, smooth, dust and grease free surface. 
* Please wait at least 3 weeks after painting walls to allow the paint to cure. 
* We recommend installation to smooth, semi-gloss or gloss enamel paint. If possible, avoid matte finish Latex paints and paints that contain anti-graffiti agents or stain blockers as well as VOC free paints, sand paints and suede paints. (please contact us for a test decal to try if you are concerned about it adhering)
* Not recommended for application to unpainted wood, textured walls, stucco, concrete, brick or over grout lines.
* Included in your order is detailed step-by-step instructions
* Please see our policies section prior to purchase
*********************************************************************************************************
SHIPPING TIME FRAMES:
ALL ORDERS ARE PROCESSED WITHIN 24 HOURS
All U.S and Canadian orders are shipped via USPS First Class. 
Any package that crosses the boarder is subject to inspection by customs. This can cause delays on the above posted shipping times. These delays are outside our control. As a result, the seller cannot guarantee shipping times.

TRACKING:
All orders will be shipped with tracking free of charge for US orders. Canadian orders will ship with tracking for a calculated cost

WHEN IS MY PACKAGE CONSIDERED LOST?
If your package is lost in the mail, we will ship you new decals. 
For Canadian orders a package is not considered lost for 45 business days from the date it is sent.
For orders to the US, a package is not considered lost for 30 business days from the date it is sent. 
(Business days are MONDAY-FRIDAY, excluding holidays)

SHIPPING ADDRESS:
Please confirm shipping address at checkout is correct. When payment is made through Paypal, we will ship to the address on file with Paypal. 
When Direct Checkout is used with Etsy, please ensure the correct address is input at checkout. 
*********************************************************************************************************
Q&A

Q. What is vinyl wall designs? 
A. It is pre-spaced designs made of very thin vinyl. A light adhesive holds each vinyl piece firmly to most hard, smooth surfaces until you're ready to remove them. Vinyl is flexible, durable and washable. All of our interior vinyl has a matte finish that allows it to blend well with your walls. These vinyl designs are not reusable or movable.

Q. What surfaces can I apply the designs to? 
A. They can be applied to clean, smooth, hard surfaces such as wood, walls, windows, mirrors, doors and even appliances such as fridges and dishwashers. 
We recommend installation to smooth, semi-gloss or gloss enamel paint. If possible, avoid matte finish Latex paints and paints that contain anti-graffiti agents or stain blockers as well as VOC free paints, sand paints and suede paints. 
Not recommended for application to unpainted wood, textured walls, stucco, panelling, concrete, brick or over grout lines.
The decal will take on the same texture as the surface it is placed on. The lettering won't adhere properly to fabric, rough surfaces, dirty walls, or to paint that isn't well bonded with the underlying surface. 
Allow new paint to dry for at least 3 weeks prior to application of the vinyl. If you would like to test our vinyl on your surface, please message us for a sample.

Q. How do I apply my wall decor?
A. We will include detailed instructions with each order. It is as easy as applying a large sticker to your wall.

Q. Can I reuse the lettering? 
A. No. The lettering is extremely thin and tends to stretch as it is being removed. Each decal is good for a one time use.

Q. Can it be used in rooms with high humidity like bathrooms?
A. Humidity doesn't affect the performance of the lettering. It works very well in bathrooms. Make sure that the surface you transfer your image to is dry and clean. 

Q. Can I use the designs outdoors? 
A. Yes. Avoid attempting to apply the vinyl in freezing conditions as the vinyl will not adhere. Also be sure that the surface is clean, dry, hard, smooth and flat. 

Q. Does it work on tile? 
A. It performs very well on tile. However, it won't work well over grout lines. 

Q. I got air bubbles in my decal when applying it?
A.The best way to remove little bubbles that don't press out under your vinyl, is by using a little straight pin or safety pin. Just poke a little hole, and press it smooth. 

Q. How do I clean my design? 
A. Use a mild household cleaner, a soft cloth or sponge, and a light touch. Avoid cleaners that contain alcohol or abrasives.
